{{Use Jamaican English|date=February 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox person |name = Gordon Obrien Swaby |image = Gordon Swaby Headshot.jpg |image_size = |caption = Self-portrait photograph |birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1990|11|18}} |birth_place = Mandeville, Manchester, Jamaica |residence = |nationality = Jamaican |ethnicity = |occupation = [[internet entrepreneur]] |known_for = Founder of Advance-Gamers and EduFocal |salary = |networth = |spouse = |children = |website = {{URL|gordonswaby.com}} |footnotes = |signature = |signature_alt = }}
'''Gordon Obrien Swaby''' (born 18 November 1990) is an internet entrepreneur based in [[Kingston, Jamaica|Kingston]], Jamaica. He is the CEO/Founder of [[EduFocal]] Limited an E-Learning web application for students at the [[CXC]] and PEP level.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-35961107|title=BBC: Turning school exams into an online game in Jamaica}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jis.gov.jm/news/100-education/30110-students-play-learn-and-win-at-edufocal |title=Students Play, Learn and Win at EduFocal |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120324231321/http://www.jis.gov.jm/news/100-education/30110-students-play-learn-and-win-at-edufocal |archivedate=24 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/magazines/career/Gordon-Swaby--dedication-personified_11643447|title= Gordon Swaby: dedication personified}}</ref>
Swaby was also the founder of the now defunct website Advance-Gamers; a large gaming website in the Caribbean at the time.<ref>[http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080721/business/business1.html The Jamaica Gleaner: Teenager makes career through game website]</ref>
Swaby is an inductee of the Branson Centre of Entrepreneurship in the Caribbean.<ref>[http://issuu.com/eZinesLimited/docs/your_money_ezine_-_march_2012/27 l EduFocal: Redefining Education through social learning]</ref><ref>[http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20120325/business/business3.html l Snapshots]</ref>
== Awards ==
Swaby is a Private Sector Organization of Jamaica (PSOJ) ''[[Jamaica Gleaner]]'' 50underFifty business leader awardee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jamaica-gleaner.com/pages/50under50/gordon-swaby.php |title=50underFifty business leader awardee |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121127144735/http://jamaica-gleaner.com/pages/50under50/gordon-swaby.php |archivedate=27 November 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> An award he won in 2012. In 2014, Gordon was named by the [[Inter-American Development Bank]] as one of ten innovators in the Latin America and Caribbean Region.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20140227/lead/lead9.html|title=Young Innovator Educating The Nation's Youth Online}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://jamaica-gleaner.com/article/news/20170716/idb-appoints-gordon-swaby-emma-lewis-civil-consulting-group|title=IDB Appoints Gordon Swaby, Emma Lewis To Civil Consulting Group}}</ref>
