{{Orphan|date=August 2017}}

'''Immersive commerce''' or '''iCommerce''' is an extension of [[E-commerce]] that focuses on improving [[Customer experience|customer experience]] by using advanced digital technology to create virtual smart stores from existing [[brick and mortar]] locations.

Rather than an iteration of traditional eCommerce,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.avantgarde.net/immersive-commerce/|title=IMMERSIVE COMMERCE, OR: RETAIL 3.0|last=Köhler|first=Ulrich|date=February 9, 2015|website=Avant Garde|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stylus.com/smjlrg|title=Virtual Immersive Commerce|last=Baron|first=Katie|date=August 27, 2014|website=Stylus|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2013/04/25/immersive-experience/#uxSeL7EB5Eqq|title=Immersing Consumers in 'Immersive Experiences'|last=Petronzio|first=Matt|date=April 25, 2013|website=Mashable|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://uxmag.com/articles/immersive-mobile-e-commerce-search-using-drop-down-menus|title=Immersive Mobile E-Commerce Search Using Drop-Down Menus|last=Nudelman|first=Greg|date=February 2, 2011|website=UX Magazine|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> iCommerce is a form of [[online shopping]] that blends physical elements of traditional stores (i.e. rows, shelves, racks, counters, etc.) with digital elements of traditional eCommerce web sites (i.e. [[mobile commerce]], [[electronic funds transfer]], [[supply chain management]], [[digital marketing]], [[online transaction processing]], [[electronic data interchange]], [[Inventory management software|inventory management systems]], [[Data collection system|automated data collection systems]] and [[Customer relationship management|CRM]]). Immersive commerce platforms give consumers the ability to browse and shop aisles of a virtual store using any online device.

Customers can view three-dimensional images of all products within a retailer's [[Stock keeping unit|SKU]] inventory. For retailers, iCommerce seeks to provide [[Omnichannel|omni-channel]] [[touchpoint]] data from the customer, including from social media, allowing retailers to continually optimize their offers in real time. It also provides retailers with an increased ability to market their brands and provides co-branding opportunities with suppliers.{{cn|date=January 2018}} 

